ijk","Walsall, Staffordshire, England":"Walsall, West Midlands, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","France":"Frankrijk"},"en":{"1132–":"1132–Deceased","1132–Male":"1132–Deceased","1132–1183":"1132–1183","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1170–Male":"1170–Deceased","1175–1241":"1175–1241","1107–1152":"1107–1152","1107":"1107","1132":"1132","1175":"1175","1241":"1241","1152":"1152","1161":"1161","1183":"1183","1170":"1170","Armston, Northamptonshire, England":"Armston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Amston, Northamptonshire, England":"Adstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Walsall, Staffordshire, England":"Walsall, West Midlands, England, United Kingdom","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ruffus","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from a place in Morayshire called Duffus.","English: nickname or topographic name from Middle English <i>douvehous</i>, <i>duffous</i> ‘dovecote’, for someone who lived by or worked in a dovehouse. It is possible that the English form of this name died out in or after the medieval period.","Possibly also an Americanized form of Dutch <b>Duffhues</b> or <b>Duifhuis</b>: topographic or habitational name referring to a house or a farm distinguished by a dovecot (compare 2 above) and named so."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Ruffus was born in 1132, in Armston, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Randulphus Ruffus. He married Matilda de le Bonnaire. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in Adstone, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1132–":"1132–Surnud","1132–Male":"1132–Surnud","1132–1183":"1132–1183","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1175–1241":"1175–1241","1107–1152":"1107–1152","1107":"1107","1132":"1132","1175":"1175","1241":"1241","1152":"1152","1161":"1161","1183":"1183","1170":"1170","Armston, Northamptonshire, England":"Armston, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Amston, Northamptonshire, England":"Adstone, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walsall, Staffordshire, England":"Walsall, West Midlands, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1132–":"1132–Kuollut","1132–Male":"1132–Kuollut","1132–1183":"1132–1183","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1175–1241":"1175–1241","1107–1152":"1107–1152","1107":"1107","1132":"1132","1175":"1175","1241":"1241","1152":"1152","1161":"1161","1183":"1183","1170":"1170","Armston, Northamptonshire, England":"Armston, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Amston, Northamptonshire, England":"Adstone, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walsall, Staffordshire, England":"Walsall, West Midlands, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1132–":"1132–Décédé","1132–Male":"1132–Décédé","1132–1183":"1132–1183","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1175–1241":"1175–1241","1107–1152":"1107–1152","1107":"1107","1132":"1132","1175":"1175","1241":"1241","1152":"1152","1161":"1161","1183":"1183","1170":"1170","Armston, Northamptonshire, England":"Armston, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni"